 this fascinating book provides the most detailed national picture of these problems. Chapters consider a range of dimensions of disadvantage as well as poverty - access to local services or employment, social relations or civic participation, health and well-being. The book also explores relationships between these in the first truly multi-dimensional analysis of exclusion. Written by leading academics, this is an authoritative account of welfare outcomes achieved across the UK. A companion volume Poverty and Social Exclusion in the UK: Volume 1 focuses on specific groups such as children or older people, and different geographical areas.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aMarginality, SocialzGreat Britain. 0aPovertyxSocial aspectszGreat Britain. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Poverty & Homelessness.2bisacsh1 aBailey, Nick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBailey, Nick, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBesemer, Kirsten, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBradshaw, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBramley, Glen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBramley, Glen, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFahmy, Eldin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFitzpatrick, Suzanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHillyard, Paddy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMack, Joanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aManley, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPantazis, Christina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPatsios, Demi, econtributor.